Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoDesign(25.10)                                              ecoDesign(25.10)

Name
       ecoDesign  -  Takes an Innovus database and a modified netlist as input
       and performs ECO operations

Syntax
        ecoDesign

       [-help]

       sessionDirectoroy

       design

       newNetList

       [-allow_to_load_binary_timing_file]

       [-addHierPortForTieOff]

       [-cpfFile <newCPFFile> | -1801File <new1801File>]

       [-def <defFile>]

       [-ecoMMMC <newMMMCFile>]

       [-ecoSDC <newSDCFile>]

       [-keepInstLoc]

       [-lef_files <LEFFilesName>]

       [-noAddFiller]

       [-skipCcopt]

       [-fillerPrefix <prefix >| -noDeleteFiller]

       [-modifyOnlyLayers <MLb:MLt>]

       [-noEcoPlace]

       [-noEcoRoute]

       [-noTiming]

       [-place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups]

       [-postMask]

       [-reportFile <reportFile>]

       [-spareCells <spareCellName>]

       [-suffix <suffix>]

       [-tieCell <cellNameList>]

       [-useGACells <GACoreSite>| -useGAFillerCells <list_of_filler_cells >]

       Takes an Innovus database and a modified netlist as input and  performs
       ECO operations. It restores the design, examines the changes in the new
       netlist,   and  automatically  implements  the  required  changes  with
       ecoPlace and ecoRoute.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each ecoDesign.

               For  a detailed description of the command and all of its para-
              meters, use the man command:

              man ecoDesign

       -1801File <new1801File>
              Specifies the name of the new 1801 file.

       -allow_to_load_binary_timing_file
              Allows the tool to load the binary timing graph  or  the  timing
              constraint file.

              If  you execute ecoDesign based on binary timing graph or timing
              constraints, the tool will give an error and  stop  loading  the
              new  design. This is because the timing graph or the timing con-
              straints file from the loaded design is a binary  file,  and  if
              you  keep  on  loading  it,  it may cause fatal error. In such a
              case, you need to restore the original design and  then  save  a
              new  design with the no-binary timing file. Then, execute ecoDe-
              sign based on the new design. If you still want to load the cur-
              rent  design,  you  need  to  run  ecoDesign  -allow_to_load_bi-
              nary_timing_file 1 to turn on the control.

       -addHierPortForTieOff
              Allows the added tie cells to connect to the tie pins across hi-
              erarchical  boundaries  if  other  constraints,  such as maximum
              fanout and maximum distance, allow it.

              This parameter can be used only with -postMask and -tieCell  op-
              tions.

       -cpfFile <newCPFFile>
              Specifies the name of the CPF file.

       -def <fileName>
              Specifies  the  DEF file you want the software to load automati-
              cally when performing ECO. This parameter automatically  assigns
              the  location of the new ECO cells. As a result, you do not need
              to run ecoPlace after performing the ECO.

       <design>
              Specifies the top cell name of the design.

       -ecoMMMC <newMMMCFile>
              Specifies the name of the new view definition file.

       -ecoSDC <newSDCFile>
              Specifies the name of the new SDC file.

       -fillerPrefix <prefix>
              Specifies the filler cell instance prefix. The ecoDesign command
              removes all filler cells before placing the ECOs. If you do  not
              specify a prefix, deleteFiller removes filler instances based on
              the  setFillerMode  command  settings.  If you have not set set-
              FillerMode, then no filler cells are removed.

       -keepInstLoc
              Keeps the instance location of changed cells.

       -lef_files <LEFFilesName>
              Specifies the LEF files name for loading. Use this option if you
              want to replace the existing LEF files in  the  original  design
              with  new  LEF files. Refer to restoreDesign -lef_files for more
              details and limitations.

              For example, tech.lef, A.lef are the existing LEFs used in orig-
              inal design. You can change A.lef to A_v2.lef using the  follow-
              ing command:

              ecoDesign  original.enc.dat  myDesign  myDesign.new.v -lef_files
              {tech.lef A_v2.lef}

       -noAddFiller
              Skips filler insertion in the pre-mask eco flow.

       -modifyOnlyLayers MLb:MLt
              Specifies the layers to be modified during the ECO process.

       <newNetList>
              Specifies the name of new netlist file.

       -noDeleteFiller
              Skips deleting filler.

       -noEcoPlace
              Prevents placement during the ECO  process.  ecoPlace  must  run
              manually based on the design's needs.

              If  you do not specify -noEcoPlace, ecoDesign calls ecoPlace in-
              ternally.

       -noEcoRoute
              Prevents routing during the ECO process.

       -noTiming
              Ignores timing libraries and MMMC configuration

       -place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups
              Specifies that filler cell instances will only  be  replaced  by
              the logic instances that belong to the same GA groups.

              This  option  can only be used when there is a filler group cre-
              ated    by     createGAFillerGroup.     ecoDesign     -place_de-
              tail_use_GA_filler_groups  first  finds the optimal location for
              each instance based on its connectivity, then searches  for  the
              nearest  GA  filler  cell  that  is  included in the same filler
              group, places a GA cell at the GA filler location,  and  deletes
              the original GA filler.

              If the GA cell is smaller than the GA filler, the placer creates
              a  new  GA  filler instance using the list of GA filler cells in
              the same filler group and places the filler in the gap.

       -postMask
              Specifies that the changes are being made on a post-mask design.

              * If you do not specify -postMask, ecoDesign runs  the  pre-mask
                flow.

              * If  you  specify  -postMask only without any GA filler option,
                tool runs the spare cell flow.

              * If you specify -postMask with any GA filler option, tool  runs
                the  GA  filler  flow. GA filler flow options are -useGACells,
                -useGAFillerCells, -place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups

              -postMask is required when option -suffix, -spareCells, -modify-
              OnlyLayers, -tieCell, or -addHierPortForTieOff is specified.

       -reportFile <reportFile       >
              Specifies the name of the report file.

              Note: By default,  ecoDesign  creates  the  default  ecoRestore-
              Design.rpt  file. However, this default file will be overwritten
              by the file name specified using the -reportFile option in  next
              eco RUN.

       <sessionDirectory>
              Specifies the .dat directory from which to load the files.

       -skipCcopt
              Skips restore ccopt config for signoffTimeDesign.

       -spareCells <spareCellName>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  spare  cell to use during the ECO
              process.

       -suffix <suffix>
              Specifies the suffix to be appended to the spare cells. You  can
              specify this parameter only if you specify -postMask.

              Default: _SPARE

       -tieCell "<cellName1> <cellName2>"
              Specifies  the  existing tie cells to be reused to make tie con-
              nections for newly created SPARE instance in the design. You can
              only specify a maximum of two tie-cells, where one cell must  be
              a  tie-high driver, and the other a tie-low driver. The two tie-
              cell names must be surrounded by quotation marks.

              This parameter can be used only with -postMask option.

       -useGACells <GA_site>
              Specifies the site name of the GA cell. Check the site name  de-
              fined in the LEF file.

       -useGAFillerCells <list_of_filler_cells>
              Specifies  a list of Gate Array (GA)-style filler cells that the
              tool can replace with GA cells during  post-mask  ECO.  You  can
              only use this parameter in a post-mask ECO flow.

              Note:  You  cannot  specify the -useGACells parameter if you use
              this parameter.

Examples
              * The following command performs a pre-mask ECO:

                ecoDesign original.enc.dat myDesign myDesign.new.v

              * The following command and options  are  used  to  implement  a
                post-mask ECO:

                ecoDesign  -postMask -modifyOnlyLayers 2:3 -spareCells *spare*
                original.enc.dat myDesign myDesign.new.v

Related Information
